that take consignments.

278
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:24,000
I'll pull together
about ten of them.

279
00:18:24,360 --> 00:18:26,520
I'll send them to you.
Pick the ones you like.

280
00:18:26,540 --> 00:18:30,200
Okay, great.
I really appreciate this.

281
00:18:30,570 --> 00:18:33,300
I know you're very busy,
and thanks for your help.

282
00:18:34,010 --> 00:18:35,360
It's nothing, Phi Mart.

283
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:37,880
Ahem.

284
00:18:38,430 --> 00:18:41,000
It's nothing, Phi Mart.

285
00:18:41,670 --> 00:18:42,960
Ouch, Dad.

286
00:18:43,330 --> 00:18:44,720
He is trying to help.

287
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:49,599
Phi Sorn, go contact the cafe today.

288
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:51,320
Wait, why me?

289
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:54,080
Well, someone has to
make the products.

290
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:57,280
Since Save and Guy helped us,
I can barely keep up.

291
00:18:57,350 --> 00:19:00,400
Can we go together
after you're done for the day?

292
00:19:00,470 --> 00:19:03,400
If you don't move fast and
someone else gets them first,

293
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:04,720
don't blame me.

294
00:19:04,860 --> 00:19:08,240
- Well...
- Yeah, Phi Sorn. Go.

295
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:12,400
It's simple. Just dropping off goods
for consignment.

296
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:15,200
Either that or you make the goods.
Can you do it?

297
00:19:15,550 --> 00:19:16,200
Well.

298
00:19:16,530 --> 00:19:20,950
Stop hemming and hawing.
Start making yourself useful.

299
00:19:38,900 --> 00:19:41,399
Hi there.
This is our vacuum cleaner.

300
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:42,879
Whisper quiet, guaranteed.

301
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:44,919
Switch it on and it won't
make a sound.

302
00:19:44,920 --> 00:19:46,480
Here, let me show you.

303
00:19:46,510 --> 00:19:48,110
- Not interested.
- Ah... just one sec.

304
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:49,960
Hey, wait. What are you doing?

305
00:19:50,580 --> 00:19:51,320
Right here.

306
00:19:51,321 --> 00:19:53,000
- Easy, easy.
- Let me show you.

307
00:19:53,030 --> 00:19:54,630
- Plug it in, turn it on.
- No.

308
00:19:54,650 --> 00:19:58,000
For your dog, it picks up pet hair
like a dream.

309
00:19:58,880 --> 00:20:00,960
This is just level one.

310
00:20:00,990 --> 00:20:03,360
- Oh, sorry. Let me turn it off.
- Get out, out.

311
00:20:04,130 --> 00:20:05,280
It's off.

312
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:07,400
Get out of here now.
I'm not buying.

313
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:08,720
I'm so sorry.

314
00:20:08,721 --> 00:20:11,519
Our water purifier runs
an RO filtration system.

315
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:14,599
High-grade membrane filtration.

316
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:17,160
Go, go. Not interested.

317
00:20:18,210 --> 00:20:22,679
Uh. The water from our purifier
does wonders for your health.

318
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:25,759
For someone your age,
the more you drink, the better.

319
00:20:25,760 --> 00:20:27,790
You'll live to see
your grandkids grow up.

320
00:20:29,580 --> 00:20:31,360
You like that now, don't you, sir?

321
00:20:31,400 --> 00:20:34,519
Which model are you interested in?
We've got plenty of options.

322
00:20:34,520 --> 00:20:36,240
Alright, stand here.

323
00:20:42,220 --> 00:20:43,920
I said I'm not buying anything.

324
00:20:43,950 --> 00:20:46,280
This is the third time this week.

325
00:20:46,310 --> 00:20:48,370
Get out.
Don't show your face here again.

326
00:20:48,400 --> 00:20:49,300
Not going?

327
00:20:49,330 --> 00:20:50,680
Ow, ow. Okay, I'm going.

328
00:20:57,400 --> 00:20:58,440
Hello, Dad.

329
00:20:58,830 --> 00:20:59,840
Well.

330
00:21:00,070 --> 00:21:03,800
What happened to you?
You're soaking wet.

331
00:21:06,130 --> 00:21:08,160
It was... hot out, Dad.

332
00:21:08,440 --> 00:21:10,880
I splashed some water on my face.

333
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:14,760
How did you do today? Good sales?

334
00:21:15,520 --> 00:21:16,520
Zero.

335
00:21:17,120 --> 00:21:21,080
Dad, I don't think
this line of work is for me.

336
00:21:21,600 --> 00:21:26,119
Already? Salesman is the easiest job
there is.

337
00:21:26,120 --> 00:21:29,640
If you can't even manage this,
how will you make a living?

338
00:21:32,120 --> 00:21:33,360
Easy, he said.

339
00:21:45,540 --> 00:21:49,000
"Quick tips for writing NC
as a beginner."

340
00:21:49,430 --> 00:21:53,840
"The most important thing
is vivid description."

341
00:21:54,140 --> 00:21:58,000
"Expressions, body language,
touch, sensation."

342
00:21:58,400 --> 00:22:01,680
"So readers can picture it
all in their heads."

343
00:22:06,630 --> 00:22:10,200
A face lost in a dream,

344
00:22:10,350 --> 00:22:13,260
lips crushed and bruised,

345
00:22:14,160 --> 00:22:17,140
flushed red,

346
00:22:17,190 --> 00:22:18,280
skin...

347
00:22:19,360 --> 00:22:20,400
slick with sweat

348
00:22:21,640 --> 00:22:24,040
grinding together

349
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:28,190
until warmth builds

350
00:22:29,130 --> 00:22:31,520
deep in the core.

351
00:22:36,940 --> 00:22:40,040
Hmm. Let me dial it up a notch.

352
00:22:42,640 --> 00:22:46,000
A face contorted

353
00:22:46,370 --> 00:22:51,560
in unbearable agony.

354
00:22:52,040 --> 00:22:58,500
Lips crushed until they split

355
00:22:59,140 --> 00:23:00,800
with the force

356
00:23:02,130 --> 00:23:04,520
of raw rage.

357
00:23:04,820 --> 00:23:06,840
The taste of blood

358
00:23:08,160 --> 00:23:11,320
seeping

359
00:23:11,350 --> 00:23:14,859
on the tip of the tongue

360
00:23:14,860 --> 00:23:18,890
sends desire surging,

361
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:23,960
flooding every inch.

362
00:23:30,180 --> 00:23:32,960
Uhm-mm. Is this too intense?

363
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:42,120
See. I can't take it anymore.

364
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:47,920
Easy. Tell me what happened.
I'm listening.

365
00:23:48,870 --> 00:23:51,040
He and his mom are so sweet.
How about that?

366
00:23:51,230 --> 00:23:54,340
So sweet that he's always
on my mind.

367
00:23:56,080 --> 00:23:58,520
I can't wait to be his.
I don't want to. Understand?

368
00:24:01,100 --> 00:24:03,040
Totally. Who wants to wait?

369
00:24:04,630 --> 00:24:07,880
Right? And I found that
he's been watching NC clips.

370
00:24:08,480 --> 00:24:11,940
Save might be looking to...
take things further, right?

371
00:24:14,320 --> 00:24:16,840
Honestly, based on
what you've said,

372
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:19,099
he sounds like a real catch.

373
00:24:19,100 --> 00:24:20,960
He probably has people lining up.

374
00:24:21,640 --> 00:24:25,360
Better make a move
before someone else does.

375
00:24:35,070 --> 00:24:38,160
Come on, dude.
You said nothing was going on.

376
00:24:38,600 --> 00:24:39,640
What's not going on?

377
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:42,200
Well, check this out.
We watched your livestream.

378
00:24:42,620 --> 00:24:45,000
Blushing and giggling,
what was that about?

379
00:24:45,150 --> 00:24:46,150
Heh.

380
00:24:47,170 --> 00:24:49,990
- Say something. We're your friends.
- Yeah.

381
00:24:50,160 --> 00:24:51,310
Read my lips.

382
00:24:51,780 --> 00:24:54,360
I'm doing it for the money.

383
00:24:55,720 --> 00:24:58,360
Guy and I, there's nothing real.
People are just shipping us.

384
00:24:58,600 --> 00:24:59,800
Are you blushing?

385
00:25:01,280 --> 00:25:02,720
Your cheeks are red too.

386
00:25:03,080 --> 00:25:04,200
I'm not blushing.

387
00:25:04,990 --> 00:25:06,520
Know any ships that
actually make it?

388
00:25:09,460 --> 00:25:10,460
Hey.

389
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:15,480
Save.

390
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:26,560
Hey, I think while we're at school,
we should keep our distance.

391
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:28,040
Why?

392
00:25:28,220 --> 00:25:31,740
Pheem, Jang, and Ron keep
teasing me, and it's getting old.

393
00:25:32,130 --> 00:25:33,130
What are they saying?

394
00:25:33,720 --> 00:25:35,040
That you're my boyfriend.

395
00:25:44,710 --> 00:25:48,880
"You can ramp up
the mood with dialogue."

396
00:25:49,140 --> 00:25:51,900
"Some readers love sound cues,
like..."

397
00:25:52,560 --> 00:25:54,360
"Umm... Ahh."

398
00:25:55,800 --> 00:25:58,440
"Owh..."

399
00:25:59,520 --> 00:26:00,520
Easy.

400
00:26:01,280 --> 00:26:02,720
I'll pop those in.

401
00:26:04,960 --> 00:26:05,960
Ooh.

402
00:26:06,710 --> 00:26:07,880
Awh.

403
00:26:08,180 --> 00:26:09,470
Does this actually work?

404
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:24,920
Ugh.

405
00:26:26,560 --> 00:26:27,560
Flat.

406
00:26:29,770 --> 00:26:32,080
Huh. This is hopeless.

407
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:34,600
Ugh.

408
00:26:46,810 --> 00:26:48,380
People keep eavesdropping.

409
00:26:49,470 --> 00:26:50,760
Hurry. We're here.

410
00:26:51,190 --> 00:26:52,190
Yeah, come on.

411
00:26:55,460 --> 00:26:56,759
Wait till we're inside.

412
00:26:56,760 --> 00:26:58,400
- Really?
- Yeah.

413
00:27:08,040 --> 00:27:12,000
Hey, really.
The lead in that series is awesome.

414
00:27:12,030 --> 00:27:13,719
- Total green flag.
- Which one?

415
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:15,760
- What series?
- Tell us.

416
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:18,160
Can't remember the title,
but I saved it. One sec.

417
00:27:18,530 --> 00:27:20,170
- Okay.
- Hurry.

418
00:27:20,190 --> 00:27:21,130
- Come on.
- Hey.

419
00:27:21,160 --> 00:27:22,160
Major green flag alert.

420
00:27:23,090 --> 00:27:25,480
- What is it?
- What?

421
00:27:25,500 --> 00:27:26,800
Don't tell me it's gone.

422
00:27:27,220 --> 00:27:28,220
- Uh oh.
- Hey.

423
00:27:31,770 --> 00:27:33,170
Is your phone at school?

424
00:27:33,300 --> 00:27:34,999
You forgot your phone?

425
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:36,000
Oh, no.

426
00:27:36,400 --> 00:27:37,740
Maybe it's still in the car?

427
00:27:40,280 --> 00:27:41,520
You left it in the car.

428
00:27:42,800 --> 00:27:43,920
Thanks, Deu.

429
00:28:05,970 --> 00:28:06,970
Here it is.

430
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:09,279
- Hey, I've seen this one.
- Hey, me too.

431
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:11,560
- But I haven't read it yet.
- Neither have I.

432
00:28:11,590 --> 00:28:13,039
You have to read it.

433
00:28:13,040 --> 00:28:14,040
- Let's go.
- Really?

434
00:28:14,060 --> 00:28:15,430
During our duty shift?

435
00:28:15,820 --> 00:28:17,100
Nobody will see us.

436
00:28:17,120 --> 00:28:19,420
- Let's go. Quickly.
- We'll read it together.

437
00:28:23,480 --> 00:28:24,919
Redder than a tomato.

438
00:28:24,920 --> 00:28:25,920
Haha.

439
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:27,960
You okay, Deu? Hot?

440
00:28:28,560 --> 00:28:29,560
No, I'm fine.

441
00:28:30,240 --> 00:28:32,240
Ready to eat? Come on.

442
00:28:32,270 --> 00:28:33,270
Hmph.

443
00:28:52,120 --> 00:28:53,120
I'm back.

444
00:28:58,920 --> 00:29:00,640
How'd it go? Did they take them?

445
00:29:04,430 --> 00:29:07,040
It's okay.
Tomorrow, you go to other shops.

446
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:08,880
One will say yes eventually.

447
00:29:12,760 --> 00:29:13,760
Okay.

448
00:29:14,940 --> 00:29:16,160
Huh.

449
00:29:54,040 --> 00:29:55,040
Grandpa.

450
00:29:56,470 --> 00:29:59,520
Ever heard of paperless?
Why not write on the computer?

451
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:01,280
Not for me.

452
00:30:05,740 --> 00:30:06,740
Hey.

453
00:30:14,280 --> 00:30:17,320
Grandpa, use the whole page.

454
00:30:23,420 --> 00:30:26,280
Why is this so hard?

455
00:30:42,800 --> 00:30:46,160
You can do it. Just imagine them
as a man and woman.

456
00:30:47,240 --> 00:30:49,360
The gender isn't the problem.

457
00:30:50,560 --> 00:30:52,680
It's that NC stuff.

458
00:30:53,320 --> 00:30:54,800
Whatever I write feels forced.

459
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:58,560
I'm trying for something subtle,
less graphic.

460
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:00,680
I'm not there yet.

461
00:31:01,520 --> 00:31:03,240
You know
what the market wants, right?

462
00:31:03,720 --> 00:31:05,960
Your readers might not
find it forced at all.

463
00:31:06,280 --> 00:31:07,920
It's got no artistry.

464
00:31:08,240 --> 00:31:09,920
Then give it some.

465
00:31:11,080 --> 00:31:12,240
You can do it.

466
00:31:18,600 --> 00:31:21,960
Honestly, I think you're just
not open to it yet.

467
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:26,640
Once you open your mind,
the words will come.

468
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:29,760
Give it a shot.

469
00:31:31,080 --> 00:31:33,080
The money's right there
in front of you.

470
00:31:34,830 --> 00:31:35,830
You've got this.

471
00:31:51,480 --> 00:31:53,000
Why the look?

472
00:31:54,080 --> 00:31:55,080
Grandpa...

473
00:31:56,980 --> 00:31:58,480
How did you get here?

474
00:31:59,000 --> 00:32:00,680
You wanted to see me, didn't you?

475
00:32:02,470 --> 00:32:04,480
I wanted to apologize for...

476
00:32:05,360 --> 00:32:08,240
not being able to take care
of Saeng Karun well enough.

477
00:32:17,850 --> 00:32:19,320
Don't blame yourself.

478
00:32:19,950 --> 00:32:22,200
Everything has its causes.

479
00:32:37,840 --> 00:32:39,920
So how's the BL novel coming along?

480
00:32:41,620 --> 00:32:43,000
Not that good, I'm afraid.

481
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:45,840
Giving up already?

482
00:32:46,520 --> 00:32:47,520
Not at all.

483
00:32:48,780 --> 00:32:49,780
Sak...

484
00:32:50,090 --> 00:32:53,400
sometimes we must push through
and do things we don't enjoy.

485
00:32:53,760 --> 00:32:56,230
If we see the benefit in it,

486
00:32:56,960 --> 00:32:59,440
we just carry on
and do what we must.

487
00:33:00,470 --> 00:33:02,200
I know that, sir.

488
00:33:04,680 --> 00:33:05,680
But...

489
00:33:06,330 --> 00:33:07,880
Take a look at this, Grandpa.

490
00:33:11,760 --> 00:33:13,880
If you were the one writing this,

491
00:33:14,680 --> 00:33:17,040
could you live with it?

492
00:33:22,160 --> 00:33:24,280
Of course. It's perfectly normal.

493
00:33:25,180 --> 00:33:26,180
Grandpa.

494
00:33:27,200 --> 00:33:29,400
This sort of thing
has been around forever.

495
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:35,120
Look at it as
love between two people.

496
00:33:35,870 --> 00:33:36,920
Sak.

497
00:33:53,410 --> 00:33:56,880
Sometimes we must push through
and do things we don't enjoy.

498
00:33:57,280 --> 00:33:59,680
But if we see the benefit in it,

499
00:34:00,520 --> 00:34:02,880
we just carry on
and do what we must.

500
00:34:06,560 --> 00:34:07,560
Hmph.

501
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:09,480
Alright.

502
00:34:37,270 --> 00:34:38,270
Fine.

503
00:34:39,110 --> 00:34:41,680
Thick skin. No shame.
Thick skin. No shame.

504
00:34:42,350 --> 00:34:44,600
For all of us at Saeng Karun.

505
00:34:47,410 --> 00:34:48,410
Hmph.

506
00:35:01,530 --> 00:35:04,000
Hello, what can I get for you?

507
00:35:04,880 --> 00:35:05,880
Um...

508
00:35:10,470 --> 00:35:12,040
Hmm...

509
00:35:13,620 --> 00:35:15,930
Americano, please.

510
00:35:16,440 --> 00:35:17,680
Of course.

511
00:35:41,340 --> 00:35:42,340
Hmph.

512
00:35:46,400 --> 00:35:47,520
"Incoming: 1."

513
00:35:50,680 --> 00:35:52,410
"Mart: I'm waiting for good news."

514
00:35:54,680 --> 00:35:55,680
Here you go.

515
00:36:19,440 --> 00:36:20,120
Um...

516
00:36:20,121 --> 00:36:22,840
Hi, can I get you anything else?

517
00:36:23,880 --> 00:36:24,880
Um...

518
00:36:27,570 --> 00:36:28,570
Um...

519
00:36:29,700 --> 00:36:31,870
Um, another Americano, please.

520
00:36:38,750 --> 00:36:40,600
Not a single shop will take it?

521
00:36:40,990 --> 00:36:41,990
No, Dad.

522
00:36:42,360 --> 00:36:45,800
Why not?
Her sweets are genuinely good.

523
00:36:47,260 --> 00:36:49,719
Did you show them our online channel

524
00:36:49,720 --> 00:36:52,160
to show how well we sell?

525
00:36:52,740 --> 00:36:54,930
I did, but...
they weren't interested.

526
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:57,800
Okay. It's fine.

527
00:36:58,240 --> 00:37:01,000
We'll try other shops tomorrow.

528
00:37:02,860 --> 00:37:03,860
Okay.

529
00:37:07,840 --> 00:37:08,840
Hey.

530
00:37:09,520 --> 00:37:12,520
Tell your wife to take a break.
She's working hard.

531
00:37:17,080 --> 00:37:19,510
Um... can I help?

532
00:37:20,220 --> 00:37:21,320
I can do it.

533
00:37:21,620 --> 00:37:24,270
While the kids are at school,
Auntie Oui helps a lot.

534
00:37:24,440 --> 00:37:25,560
Take some rest.

535
00:37:25,590 --> 00:37:27,760
No. These must get done.

536
00:37:29,140 --> 00:37:29,910
Ow.

537
00:37:29,940 --> 00:37:31,240
- Hey, hey.
- Ouch.

538
00:37:31,510 --> 00:37:32,640
- I knew it.
- Mart.

539
00:37:33,380 --> 00:37:34,300
- Look.
- Ow.

540
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:38,729
Take her to the doctor.
This is the second time today.

541
00:37:38,730 --> 00:37:39,730
Whew.

542
00:37:40,230 --> 00:37:42,910
Sorn, take her to the doctor.

543
00:37:42,940 --> 00:37:43,940
Yes, yes.

544
00:37:45,890 --> 00:37:47,159
Hold down the fort, Auntie Oui.

545
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:48,160
Got it. Got it.

546
00:37:48,730 --> 00:37:49,730
Easy now.

547
00:37:58,580 --> 00:37:59,580
Ow.

548
00:38:01,520 --> 00:38:02,520
Ouch.

549
00:38:03,300 --> 00:38:04,300
Ugh.

550
00:38:05,540 --> 00:38:06,440
Does it hurt here?

551
00:38:06,510 --> 00:38:07,920
Yes, Doctor.

552
00:38:09,080 --> 00:38:10,280
Please lie on your back.

553
00:38:30,700 --> 00:38:33,640
Any numbness or
trouble with bladder control?

554
00:38:34,840 --> 00:38:35,840
No.

555
00:38:35,990 --> 00:38:38,840
You have inflammation
of the back muscles.

556
00:38:39,490 --> 00:38:42,560
The bones and nerves are fine.

557
00:38:43,070 --> 00:38:45,470
Can I still make sweets?

558
00:38:45,780 --> 00:38:48,680
I'd recommend resting for now.

559
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:52,520
If you keep lifting heavy things
or straining those muscles,

560
00:38:52,800 --> 00:38:54,200
the inflammation will get worse.

561
00:38:54,820 --> 00:38:57,080
- But...
- Listen to the doctor.

562
00:38:58,500 --> 00:39:00,440
How am I supposed to stop?

563
00:39:00,720 --> 00:39:03,399
People have already paid
for their orders.

564
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:04,920
We have to hold up our end.

565
00:39:05,700 --> 00:39:08,080
The doctor says to stop.
So you stop.

566
00:39:08,560 --> 00:39:10,530
So, what's the treatment?

567
00:39:11,800 --> 00:39:14,170
I'll prescribe medication
and a topical cream

568
00:39:14,400 --> 00:39:15,690
to reduce the inflammation,

569
00:39:15,920 --> 00:39:18,320
combined with complete rest
of that muscle group.

570
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:39,720
Slowly. Slowly.

571
00:39:40,200 --> 00:39:41,320
Easy. Easy.

572
00:39:42,010 --> 00:39:43,440
Come here. This way.

573
00:39:44,370 --> 00:39:45,640
- Here.
- Ow.

574
00:39:45,890 --> 00:39:46,890
Step down.

575
00:39:47,230 --> 00:39:48,240
Slowly.

576
00:39:50,590 --> 00:39:53,240
Oh... ugh.

577
00:39:53,740 --> 00:39:55,279
Okay, shift left a little.

578
00:39:55,280 --> 00:39:56,320
Shift left.

579
00:39:56,540 --> 00:39:57,760
Easy. Easy.

580
00:39:58,320 --> 00:39:59,320
Easy.

581
00:40:00,960 --> 00:40:02,120
Come here.

582
00:40:02,480 --> 00:40:03,600
I'm going to carry you.

583
00:40:03,630 --> 00:40:06,439
Oh, no, no. What are you doing?

584
00:40:06,440 --> 00:40:08,560
I don't need that. I can still walk.

585
00:40:08,590 --> 00:40:10,240
- Oh really?
- Yes.

586
00:40:10,500 --> 00:40:11,500
Then your arm.

587
00:40:12,030 --> 00:40:13,799
That back of yours
would give out too.

588
00:40:13,800 --> 00:40:14,800
Give me your hand.

589
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:16,720
- Okay?
- Yeah.

590
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:18,960
Hmm.

591
00:40:19,770 --> 00:40:20,770
Ow.

592
00:40:22,520 --> 00:40:23,640
Hold this. Hold.

593
00:40:25,340 --> 00:40:26,920
Take your time. No rush.

594
00:40:38,060 --> 00:40:39,060
You okay?

595
00:40:39,310 --> 00:40:40,310
Mm-hmm.

596
00:40:47,090 --> 00:40:48,320
Huh.

597
00:40:53,490 --> 00:40:54,600
- Mart.
- Hmm?

598
00:40:55,420 --> 00:40:57,200
You've been running yourself
into the ground.

599
00:40:58,080 --> 00:40:59,120
Just rest, okay?

600
00:41:01,600 --> 00:41:04,040
What's with you,
going all sentimental?

601
00:41:07,080 --> 00:41:10,000
Listen. Don't worry about a thing.

602
00:41:10,130 --> 00:41:11,910
I'll handle the consignment.

603
00:41:16,120 --> 00:41:17,120
Mom.

604
00:41:19,870 --> 00:41:21,520
Aw, aw. Easy.

605
00:41:23,200 --> 00:41:24,200
Hmm.

606
00:41:25,340 --> 00:41:28,620
I told you not to lift heavy things.

607
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:32,680
Please don't scold a sick person.

608
00:41:33,680 --> 00:41:34,800
- Mom.
- Hmm?

609
00:41:35,260 --> 00:41:38,520
Does it hurt anywhere?
I'll give you a massage.

610
00:41:40,630 --> 00:41:41,630
Save.

611
00:41:42,260 --> 00:41:44,400
Thanks so much
for picking up the kids.

612
00:41:44,680 --> 00:41:45,680
Mm-hmm.

613
00:41:46,350 --> 00:41:47,720
Are you holding up?

614
00:41:48,760 --> 00:41:50,600
Don't go coming down
with something too.

615
00:41:51,070 --> 00:41:53,200
Hmm. I'm fine.

616
00:41:55,170 --> 00:41:56,400
Look after Mom, will you?

617
00:41:57,530 --> 00:41:58,530
I'll be right in.

618
00:42:57,500 --> 00:42:58,500
Huh.

619
00:43:00,180 --> 00:43:01,180
Let's go.

620
00:43:05,760 --> 00:43:07,800
Oh, excuse me.

621
00:43:07,820 --> 00:43:08,920
Excuse me.

622
00:43:11,880 --> 00:43:13,100
Can I help you?

623
00:43:13,120 --> 00:43:14,480
Um, well, here's the thing.

624
00:43:17,980 --> 00:43:19,120
It's just that...

625
00:43:20,420 --> 00:43:22,560
I'd like to consign
some sweets here.

626
00:43:22,780 --> 00:43:24,180
Who should I talk to, please?

627
00:43:34,520 --> 00:43:35,520
Hang in there.

628
00:43:36,920 --> 00:43:37,920
Just hang in there.

629
00:44:05,560 --> 00:44:06,720
Phi Save.

630
00:44:07,420 --> 00:44:09,860
My friend wants to know...
if you're single.

631
00:44:14,310 --> 00:44:15,310
Um.

632
00:44:16,240 --> 00:44:18,480
Your friend... or you?

633
00:44:18,920 --> 00:44:20,000
Puean (friend).

634
00:44:20,520 --> 00:44:21,760
My name is Puean.

635
00:44:24,240 --> 00:44:25,240
I'm single.

636
00:44:25,490 --> 00:44:26,400
Hmm?

637
00:44:26,401 --> 00:44:27,440
Ahem.

638
00:44:29,200 --> 00:44:30,840
Here you go. Enjoy.

639
00:44:32,340 --> 00:44:33,340
Thanks.

640
00:44:52,290 --> 00:44:54,360
- Must be smooth like this. See?
- Hey.

641
00:44:55,100 --> 00:44:56,520
The doctor told you to rest.

642
00:44:56,880 --> 00:44:57,880
- Heh.
- Hmm?

643
00:45:01,000 --> 00:45:04,360
Phi Sorn, how did it go?
Any shops take it?

644
00:45:06,240 --> 00:45:07,240
Huh.

645
00:45:07,520 --> 00:45:08,520
Again?

646
00:45:09,360 --> 00:45:12,240
It's okay.
We'll keep streaming for now.

647
00:45:17,400 --> 00:45:20,039
Three shops agreed to
carry our sweets.

648
00:45:20,040 --> 00:45:21,040
- What?
- What?

649
00:45:21,300 --> 00:45:23,320
- Are you serious?
- Of course.

650
00:45:23,540 --> 00:45:24,320
Hey.

651
00:45:24,520 --> 00:45:27,920
Sorn, don't mess around.

652
00:45:28,080 --> 00:45:31,040
I'm not messing around.
They really took us in.

653
00:45:31,070 --> 00:45:32,280
- Yay.
- Alright.

654
00:45:32,310 --> 00:45:35,320
- Oh, aww.
- Hey, easy. Sit down.

655
00:45:35,350 --> 00:45:38,160
Ow... hehe. I got carried away.

656
00:45:38,930 --> 00:45:42,320
I'll help handle the orders
going to those shops.

657
00:45:47,430 --> 00:45:48,600
- Dad.
- Hmm?

658
00:45:48,800 --> 00:45:50,040
I made it.

659
00:45:51,290 --> 00:45:52,290
It's nothing.

660
00:45:53,660 --> 00:45:55,600
Heh.

661
00:46:05,430 --> 00:46:06,680
- Okay.
- Come here.

662
00:46:13,500 --> 00:46:15,200
My turn now.

663
00:46:17,790 --> 00:46:18,790
Here.

664
00:46:19,370 --> 00:46:20,680
It's good. You want some?

665
00:46:25,160 --> 00:46:27,480
What's up? You swallowed a lemon?

666
00:46:28,940 --> 00:46:30,120
Did that guy flirt with you?

667
00:46:31,240 --> 00:46:32,319
Probably.

668
00:46:32,320 --> 00:46:33,320
What do you think?

669
00:46:33,880 --> 00:46:34,880
Think about what?

670
00:46:35,040 --> 00:46:36,160
Do you like him?

671
00:46:38,040 --> 00:46:39,520
Don't tell me you're jealous.

672
00:46:41,840 --> 00:46:43,080
What if I am?

673
00:46:46,440 --> 00:46:48,800
Why would you be jealous?

674
00:46:49,240 --> 00:46:50,420
Don't I have the right to be?

675
00:46:52,120 --> 00:46:53,700
Come on. It was just for fun.

676
00:46:54,350 --> 00:46:55,520
Come on. Let's go home.

677
00:47:09,400 --> 00:47:13,120
If I asked to make it official now,
what are the odds he'd say yes?

678
00:47:14,880 --> 00:47:16,480
99.9 percent.

679
00:47:33,760 --> 00:47:34,760
Save.

680
00:47:36,760 --> 00:47:37,880
Will you be my boyfriend?

681
00:47:37,910 --> 00:47:38,910
Sorry?

682
00:47:42,080 --> 00:47:43,080
Hey...

683
00:47:44,400 --> 00:47:45,800
thanks a lot for...

684
00:47:46,600 --> 00:47:47,800
asking me that.

685
00:47:48,610 --> 00:47:49,800
But I'm not ready.

686
00:47:52,200 --> 00:47:54,640
Yeah, I kind of figured.

687
00:47:55,720 --> 00:47:57,040
I braced myself for it.

688
00:47:57,670 --> 00:47:59,040
But you still asked anyway.

689
00:48:00,240 --> 00:48:01,600
Better than not asking, right?

690
00:48:03,440 --> 00:48:04,870
You're not upset with me, right?

691
00:48:06,200 --> 00:48:07,200
Why would I be?

692
00:48:09,120 --> 00:48:11,080
See, you're so hard to read.

693
00:48:11,330 --> 00:48:12,840
I just wanted to try my luck.

694
00:48:13,640 --> 00:48:14,680
And?

695
00:48:15,800 --> 00:48:16,800
Shot down.

696
00:48:23,800 --> 00:48:24,960
When the time is right,

697
00:48:25,920 --> 00:48:26,980
I'll let you know.

698
00:48:31,250 --> 00:48:33,910
Okay, then I'll just keep asking.

699
00:48:34,320 --> 00:48:35,440
Won't you get tired of it?

700
00:48:38,160 --> 00:48:41,000
By all means. If you can take it.

701
00:48:49,520 --> 00:48:50,520
Save.

702
00:49:03,760 --> 00:49:05,639
See? You can eat them.
Won't kill you.

703
00:49:05,640 --> 00:49:08,600
It's actually good, Deu. Refreshing.

704
00:49:09,320 --> 00:49:11,080
Stop lying. Not buying it.

705
00:49:13,520 --> 00:49:16,199
Fine. No tomato, no soccer.

706
00:49:16,200 --> 00:49:18,160
We need backup, Deu.

707
00:49:18,640 --> 00:49:21,840
If we lose to Phi Guy,
Saeng Karun's pride goes with it.

708
00:49:35,400 --> 00:49:37,040
Fine, don't eat it then.

709
00:49:37,070 --> 00:49:39,640
Stay off the field
for the rest of your life, Deu.

710
00:49:40,000 --> 00:49:41,440
Fine, I won't play then.

711
00:49:41,560 --> 00:49:43,640
I won't forget
you ditched your friends, Deu.

712
00:49:45,200 --> 00:49:46,640
You're not my friend.

713
00:49:47,520 --> 00:49:48,520
Pipe.

714
00:49:49,560 --> 00:49:50,920
Can we play with you today?

715
00:49:50,950 --> 00:49:52,400
What? For real?

716
00:49:52,830 --> 00:49:55,860
Yeah, yesterday the teacher told us
about female soccers.

717
00:49:55,910 --> 00:49:57,040
Made me want to try it.

718
00:50:16,480 --> 00:50:17,840
I'll do soccer now, sir.

719
00:50:30,850 --> 00:50:32,359
Snow, let's go.

720
00:50:32,360 --> 00:50:35,120
- Pipe, let me play.
- Snow, you've got this.

721
00:50:35,940 --> 00:50:37,399
You ate your tomato?

722
00:50:37,400 --> 00:50:38,400
Yeah, I did.

723
00:50:38,620 --> 00:50:39,620
Cool.

724
00:50:43,980 --> 00:50:45,040
Snow, you've got this.

725
00:50:45,060 --> 00:50:46,240
Deu, over here.

726
00:50:46,580 --> 00:50:49,959
Snow, you can do it.

727
00:50:49,960 --> 00:50:50,960
Go, Snow.

728
00:50:50,990 --> 00:50:57,070
Snow, go, go.

729
00:50:58,220 --> 00:51:03,160
- Yay.
- Hooray.

730
00:51:09,640 --> 00:51:11,440
So how was the tomato?

731
00:51:13,450 --> 00:51:14,840
Disgusting, Grandpa.

732
00:51:16,060 --> 00:51:16,880
But...

733
00:51:17,050 --> 00:51:18,050
But what?

734
00:51:18,070 --> 00:51:21,430
Not as bad as I thought.
I'll live with it.

735
00:51:22,140 --> 00:51:29,210
Snow, let's do it.

736
00:51:42,780 --> 00:51:45,320
Three shops agreed to
carry our sweets.

737
00:51:45,600 --> 00:51:46,600
- What?
- What?

738
00:51:46,700 --> 00:51:48,719
- Are you serious?
- Of course.

739
00:51:48,720 --> 00:51:49,920
I made it.

740
00:51:50,360 --> 00:51:52,840
Disgusting, Grandpa. But...

741
00:51:53,120 --> 00:51:54,159
But what?

742
00:51:54,160 --> 00:51:57,600
But not as bad as I thought.
I'll live with it.

743
00:52:08,930 --> 00:52:11,840
Stories with NC scenes
sell exceptionally well.

744
00:52:12,050 --> 00:52:15,650
Once you open your mind,
the words will come.

745
00:52:16,490 --> 00:52:18,680
The money's right there
in front of you.

746
00:52:19,040 --> 00:52:20,599
Principal and interest

747
00:52:20,600 --> 00:52:25,200
come to 12,508,649.75 baht.

748
00:52:25,640 --> 00:52:29,040
Sometimes we must push through
and do things we don't enjoy.

749
00:52:29,410 --> 00:52:30,080
Hmph.

750
00:52:30,081 --> 00:52:33,439
Accounts over 180 days past due

751
00:52:33,440 --> 00:52:37,160
will be subject to legal action.

752
00:52:37,560 --> 00:52:38,600
I'm not afraid.

753
00:52:39,350 --> 00:52:42,440
Every scene needs
to be steaming hot.

754
00:52:42,900 --> 00:52:44,320
I am that dang good.

755
00:52:45,830 --> 00:52:46,830
Hm... hm.

756
00:52:50,820 --> 00:52:52,090
Muahaha.

757
00:53:07,280 --> 00:53:09,479
I ain't writing anymore.

758
00:53:09,480 --> 00:53:14,760
Hngh. Hngh.

759
00:53:14,830 --> 00:53:17,640
At his age, he doesn't need to work.

760
00:53:17,820 --> 00:53:19,260
Just sit around and that's it.

761
00:53:19,840 --> 00:53:23,360
Right. He can barely even walk now.

762
00:53:23,390 --> 00:53:25,120
You promised Khun Tiad, right?

763
00:53:26,000 --> 00:53:27,440
Don't you feel guilty?

764
00:53:28,040 --> 00:53:30,960
I said I'm done. I quit.

765
00:53:32,150 --> 00:53:34,640
You can go now.
We've come as far as we can.

766
00:53:34,680 --> 00:53:40,559
The world keeps
turning every day.

767
00:53:40,560 --> 00:53:45,959
And we keep turning in its play.

768
00:53:45,960 --> 00:53:49,239
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

769
00:53:49,240 --> 00:53:51,759
We just might see
the world within.

770
00:53:51,760 --> 00:53:55,879
Let's walk together, day by day.

771
00:53:55,880 --> 00:54:00,880
Come take the step,
what do you say?

772
00:54:07,440 --> 00:54:10,959
Let us be real,
not dreaming away,

773
00:54:10,960 --> 00:54:14,999
We'll walk in the light
of a new day.

774
00:54:15,000 --> 00:54:19,999
No one can tell
what tomorrow may say.

775
00:54:20,000 --> 00:54:22,479
Wherever the gentle wind blows,

776
00:54:22,480 --> 00:54:25,239
let our hearts flow,
soft and slow.

777
00:54:25,240 --> 00:54:30,080
And land where
our hearts both grow.

778
00:54:30,500 --> 00:54:36,319
The world keeps
turning every day.

779
00:54:36,320 --> 00:54:41,559
And we keep turning in its play.

780
00:54:41,560 --> 00:54:44,880
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

781
00:54:45,160 --> 00:54:47,679
We just might see
the world within.

782
00:54:47,680 --> 00:54:51,759
Let's walk together, day by day.

783
00:54:51,760 --> 00:54:56,880
Come take the step,
what do you say?

